s, with patient-specific vascular geometries\nharboring IAs, were carried out using the one-way fluid-solid interaction\nsolution strategy, in which the blood flow is solved and applied as the driving\nforce of the wall motion. We found that different wall morphology models yield\nsmaller absolute differences in the mechanical response than different\nhyperelastic laws. Furthermore, the stretch levels of IAs walls were more\nsensitive to the hyperelastic and material constants than the stress. These\nfindings could be used to guide modeling decisions on IA simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Oct 2022 16:09:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-12"}
