easurements, as well as significant difference in measurements\nperformed with NTE = 4 and NTE = 8 echoes (P < 0.0001 in chest fat and P < 0.01\nin pericardial fat). CONCLUSION Volunteer experiments at 1.5T demonstrated the\nfeasibility of a whole-heart free-running fat-fraction mapping technique for\ncardiac MRI in a 6 min scan time, with a resolution of 2mm3 isotropic.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Oct 2022 12:38:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Feb 2023 14:59:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 12 Apr 2023 08:51:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-13"}
